rht</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs Robert Lainham was born about 1340, in England, United Kingdom. She married Robert Lainham. They were the parents of at least 1 son."},"et":{"Abt 1340–":"umbes 1340–Surnud","1330–Male":"1330–Surnud","1360–1418":"1360–1418","1340–Female":"1340–Surnud","Abt 1340":"umbes 1340","1330":"1330","1340":"1340","1360":"1360","1418":"1418","Of England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Essex, England":"Essex, England"},"fi":{"Abt 1340–":"noin 1340–Kuollut","1330–Male":"1330–Kuollut","1360–1418":"1360–1418","1340–Female":"1340–Kuollut","Abt 1340":"noin 1340","1330":"1330","1340":"1340","1360":"1360","1418":"1418","Of England":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Essex, England":"Essex, England"},"fr":{"Abt 1340–":"environ 1340–Décédée","1330–Male":"1330–Décédé","1360–1418":"1360–1418","1340–Female":"1340–Décédée","Abt 1340":"environ 1340","1330":"1330","1340":"1340","1360":"1360","1418":"1418","Of England":"Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Essex, England":"Essex, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Mrs Robert Lainham est née environ 1340, à Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Elle a épousé Robert Lainham. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fils."},"de":{"Abt 1340–":"um 1340–Verstorben","1330–Male":"1330–Verstorben","1360–1418":"1360–1418","1340–Female":"1340–Verstorben","Abt 1340":"um 1340","1330":"1330","1340":"1340","1360":"1360","1418":"1418","Of England":"England, United Kingdom","Essex, England":"Essex, England","lifeSummary":"Mrs Robert Lainham wurde u